{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Sauce","content":["Place mushrooms into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add onions, garlic and oil and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>2 min\/250°F\/speed 1<b>.","Add tomatoes and salt, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <b>10 min\/250°F\/speed 1<b>. Remove simmering basket, insert measuring cup and blend <b>4 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer sauce to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Toppings","content":["Place mozzarella and cheddar cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place sausage into mixing bowl and cook <b>4 min\/250°F\/\/speed 0.5<b>. Mix well with spatula and cook a further <b>4 min\/250°F\/\/speed 1<b>. Line a bowl with paper towels. Transfer cooked sausage into bowl and let drain. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Dough","content":["Place flour, water, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>, then knead <b>2 min\/<b>.","Transfer dough to a lightly floured surface. Cut dough into six equal pieces and shape each piece into a ball. Cover with a damp paper towel and let rest 10 minutes. Meanwhile preheat oven to 425°F and line two baking sheets with parchment.","Roll out each piece of dough into a circle (approx. 6 in.). Transfer dough circles onto prepared baking sheets and brush with oil. Prebake pizza dough for 5 minutes (425°F) before adding toppings.","Evenly divide and spread reserved sauce over each pizza dough, leaving a ½ inch border. Top with onions, reserved cheese and reserved sausage. Crack one egg directly onto each pizza, nestled into toppings. Bake for 5-7 minutes (425°F) until eggs are set to taste and pizza edges are puffed and lightly golden. Let rest 3-5 minutes before slicing. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Sauce","content":["½ oz dried mushrooms","4 oz red onions, cut into pieces","1 garlic clove","1 tbsp olive oil","9 oz tomatoes, cut into pieces","¼ tsp salt"]},{"title":"Toppings","content":["2 oz mozzarella, cubed (1 in.)","2 oz cheddar cheese, cubed (1 in.)","8 oz uncooked breakfast sausage, casing removed, crumbled or cut into pieces"]},{"title":"Dough","content":["11 ½ oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust","7 ½ oz water","1 tsp baking powder","½ tsp salt","2 tsp olive oil","4 oz red onions, thinly sliced half-moons, divided","6 eggs, divided","Italian parsley, to garnish"]}],"id":"r343849","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Fw0XSDOKgHE\/XZQFpYgyAtI\/AAAAAAAAb1I\/3TNz9wIGNiosOdpNO_vQ3LqdFFNhlGWDACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8QrPSe2RhbCw8cKK.png","title":"Breakfast Sausage Pizzas","publishedAt":"2018-05-04T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"28 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"51 g","calories":"2272 kJ \/ 543 kcal"},"usefulItems":"paper towels, parchment paper, rolling pin, baking sheets, pastry brush, oven","basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}